Create a Recipe with Data Prep

Use a Data Prep recipe in CRM Analytics to clean, transform, and enrich data before loading data into one or more targets. To ensure you’re building the right logic, preview the results as you build it.

From Data Manager, click Recipes or Dataflows & Recipes.
To create a recipe, click Create Recipe.
Review the Data Prep welcome mat, and then click X to close it.

Optionally, click Learn More to get more information about Data Prep.

To choose the initial input data for the recipe, click Select Data.
Select the checkbox next to each dataset, connected object, or direct data that you want to add as input for the recipe.

A direct data reference doesn’t store data in CRM Analytics. Each time a recipe uses direct data, a query gets the current data.

You can’t use a trended dataset as input data for a recipe. If needed, you can add more data to the recipe later.

In the Selected Columns area on the right, choose either Custom Columns to include selected columns or All Columns to include all available columns from the chosen dataset.

To add transformations and nodes, click on the Graph area.
To save the recipe, click Save.
Enter a recipe name and description, and then click Save again.

Nodes for Data Prep Recipes
In CRM Analytics, Data Prep provides nodes that allow you to bring in data, transform it, and write the results to a target. 

Transformations for Data Prep Recipes
In CRM Analytics, Data Prep provides transformations that allow you to prepare, clean, and transform your data.

Connect and Reorganize Nodes or Branches in a Recipe
In CRM Analytics, connect disconnected nodes or branches to join or append data from any node to any other node in a Data Prep recipe.

Copy and Paste a Recipe
In CRM Analytics, use the toolbar or keyboard shortcuts to copy and paste nodes within a single recipe or across multiple ones.
